</head>
<body>

    

    <div class="recipe-container">
        <h1>🌶️ Crispy Gobi Manchurian Recipe</h1>
       
        <h2>Ingredients:</h2>
        <ul class="ingredients-list">
            <li>1 medium Cauliflower (Gobi), cut into florets</li>
            <li>½ cup All-purpose Flour (Maida)</li>
            <li>¼ cup Corn Flour</li>
            <li>1 tsp Ginger-Garlic Paste</li>
            <li>1 tsp Red Chili Powder</li>
            <li>½ tsp Pepper Powder</li>
            <li>Salt to taste</li>
            <li>Water as required</li>
            <li>Oil for deep frying</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>For Manchurian Sauce:</h2>
        <ul class="ingredients-list">
            <li>2 tbsp Oil</li>
            <li>1 Onion, finely chopped</li>
            <li>1 Capsicum, diced</li>
            <li>2 tbsp Garlic, minced</li>
            <li>2 tbsp Soy Sauce</li>
            <li>1 tbsp Tomato Ketchup</li>
            <li>1 tbsp Chili Sauce</li>
            <li>1 tbsp Vinegar</li>
            <li>1 tsp Sugar</li>
            <li>2 tbsp Cornflour slurry (cornflour mixed with water)</li>
            <li>Spring Onion for garnish</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Instructions:</h2>
        <ol class="instructions-list">
            <li>Mix flour, cornflour, ginger-garlic paste, chili powder, pepper, and salt with water to form a thick batter.</li>
            <li>Dip the cauliflower florets into the batter and deep fry until crispy.</li>
            <li>Heat oil in a pan and sauté garlic, onion, and capsicum.</li>
            <li>Add soy sauce, chili sauce, tomato ketchup, vinegar, sugar, and mix well.</li>
            <li>Pour in the cornflour slurry and stir until the sauce thickens.</li>
            <li>Add the crispy fried cauliflower and toss well to coat evenly.</li>
            <li>Garnish with chopped spring onions and serve hot.</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

</body>
</html>
